==English==

===Pronunciation===
*wā, /weɪ/, /weI/
*:'''Homophones''': [[way]], [[whey]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-eɪ|Rhymes: -eɪ]]

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|weigh||}}
# To determine the weight of an object. 
# ''(metaphorical)'' To determine the intrinsic value or merit of an object
#:''You have been '''weighed''' in the balance and found wanting.''
# To consider a subject. 
# (''Nautical'') To raise an anchor free of the seabed.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[punnita]] (1)
*French: [[peser]] (1,2,3), [[lever]] (l'ancre) (4)
*Swedish: [[väga]] (1,2)

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|weigh||}}
# The amount of gravitational force exerted by mass.
#:''How much do you '''weigh'''?''

